# WKS Platform — tracked dev defaults (Story 14.1.1 AC1).
#
# This file is COMMITTED to the repo so the documented zero-config dev quick-start
# (`docker compose up`) keeps working after the dev `wks-platform` service was scoped
# to `profiles: [dev]` (finding C5: without `profiles:`, the dev service ran for every
# profile selection and collided with `wks-platform-prod` on host port 8080).
#
# Compose semantics: services with `profiles:` only start when their profile is selected.
# `COMPOSE_PROFILES=dev` selects the dev profile by default. `docker compose up` therefore
# brings up the dev service without any operator action.
#
# Production operators OVERWRITE this file with their own secrets (canonical path:
# `cp docker/.env.production.example docker/.env`, then fill in values). The example
# file sets `COMPOSE_PROFILES=production` so that copy flips the profile selection
# automatically.
#
# This tracked file MUST NOT carry secrets. Add only non-secret defaults here.

COMPOSE_PROFILES=dev
